HB 12 Original 2026 Regular Session Villio
Abstract: Extends survival benefits to the surviving spouse of a reserve or auxiliary law
enforcement officer.
Present law provides for $250,000 in survivor benefits to the spouse or other legal survivor
of a fireman or law enforcement officer in certain circumstances.
Proposed law retains present law and extends survivor benefits to the spouse or other legal
survivor of a reserve or auxiliary law enforcement officer.
(Amends R.S. 40:1665.2(F))
